From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: server: park gapped posted messages + WM_USER storm duty-cycle breaker

Two cooperating mechanisms against the X50II JUCE menu storm (see memory
feedback_x50_stomp_popup_grab_dismiss for the full trace):

1. PARK GAPPED POSTS (the actual fix, default ON, WINE_VSTPOC_PARK_POSTED=0
   to disable): patch 030's WINE_VSTPOC_POST_GAP_MS suppresses WM_USER+
   delivery but leaves the messages pending, so QS_POSTMESSAGE stays set and
   the guest's GetMessage never blocks - it busy-polls the server (X50II
   menu storm: thousands of NtUserPeekMessage round-trips/s, vst_host 59% +
   wineserver 67% CPU, X server idle, UI starved, audio xruns). When the
   gap suppresses delivery, clear the posted wake bits and re-arm them with
   a server timeout at gap end. The thread then truly sleeps; the JUCE
   self-feed loop still runs but at a harmless ~20 deliveries/s. Hardware
   input and sent messages have their own QS bits and still wake the
   thread, so interaction stays live.

2. WM_USER RATE BREAKER (defense in depth, WINE_VSTPOC_USER_STORM_BREAK=
   <deliveries/s>, unset/0 = off): for configurations running WITHOUT a
   flat post gap, count WM_USER+ deliveries per queue in a rolling 1s
   window; above the threshold, suppress WM_USER+ delivery for 250ms
   (parked the same way). Storms run >1000/s, legit JUCE repaint bursts
   ~60-120/s. CAUTION: thresholds low enough to trip during editor INIT
   starve JUCE's init callbacks and can crash plugins (X50II crashed at
   threshold 5); keep >= 500.

